transcript: Walter White and Jesse Pinkman have a complex, dynamic relationship that evolves throughout "Breaking Bad." Initially, it's a mentor-student relationship, with Walt as the experienced chemistry teacher and Jesse as the ex-student-turned-drug dealer. However, as they dive deeper into the drug trade, their relationship becomes more of a partnership, albeit a volatile and often manipulative one. Walt frequently manipulates Jesse, who struggles with his own moral dilemmas and addiction issues. Their bond is marked by mutual dependence, deep-seated resentment, and occasional moments of genuine care and loyalty, making it one of the most intriguing and tumultuous relationships on the show.
